  <sect1 id="monkey-bubble-introduction"> 
    <title>Introduction</title> 
    <para>
      <application>&app;</application> is an arcade game with the following objectives :
    </para>

    <variablelist> 
      <varlistentry> 
	<term>Clear the jungle from all those nasty bubbles</term> 
	<listitem> 
	  <para>
	    To clear a level, you need to stick at least 3 bubbles of the same
	    color together using the bubble shooter.
	  </para>
	  <para>
	    Once 3 or more bubbles of the color are sticked together
	    at the top of the playground, they will explode.
	  </para>
	  <para>
	    To level up, you need to clear all the bubbles stuck in the playground.
	  </para>
	</listitem> 
      </varlistentry> 
    </variablelist> 
  </sect1> 

  <sect1 id="monkey-bubble-get-started"> 
    <title>Getting Started</title> 
    <para>
      The following sections describe how to start 
      <application>&app;</application>. 
    </para>
    <sect2 id="gnome-terminal-to-start"> 
      <title>To Start &app;</title> 
      <para>
	You can start <application>&app;</application> in the following ways: 
      </para>
      <variablelist> 
	<varlistentry> 
	  <term>Applications menu</term> 
	  <listitem>
	    <para>
	      Choose
	      <menuchoice>
		<guimenu>Games</guimenu>
		<guimenuitem>Monkey Bubble</guimenuitem>
	      </menuchoice>.</para>
	  </listitem>
	</varlistentry> 
	<varlistentry> 
	  <term>Command line</term> 
	  <listitem> 
	    <para>
	      Execute the following command: <command>monkey-bubble</command>
	    </para>
	  </listitem> 
	</varlistentry> 
      </variablelist> 
    </sect2> 
  </sect1> 
